friends.name: The One Where It All Began
friends.summary: Monica's old friend Rachel moves in with her after leaving her fianc√©.

friends.name: The One With the Sonogram at the End
friends.summary: Rachel returns her engagement ring; Ross's ex-wife has a revelation for him.

friends.name: The One With the Thumb
friends.summary: Monica's friends find her new beau appealing; Phoebe finds a little something extra in her soda.

friends.name: The One With George Stephanopoulos
friends.summary: Chandler and Joey take Ross to a hockey game -- with painful results; the ladies get someone else's pizza.

friends.name: The One With the East German Laundry Detergent
friends.summary: Ross does laundry with Rachel; Joey uses Monica to get his old girlfriend back.

friends.name: The One With the Butt
friends.summary: Joey's new agent gets him a cheeky role in a movie; Chandler dates a woman with lots of baggage.

friends.name: The One With the Blackout
friends.summary: A blackout traps Chandler in an ATM vestibule with model Jill Goodacre; a cat comes between Ross and Rachel.

friends.name: The One Where Nana Dies Twice
friends.summary: Monica and Ross mourn the loss of their grandmother.

friends.name: The One Where Underdog Gets Away
friends.summary: Monica tries to cook Thanksgiving dinner for the gang; Ross relishes the chance to talk to his unborn child.

friends.name: The One With the Monkey
friends.summary: A new pet monkeys around with Ross's ego during the holidays; Phoebe falls for a scientist .

friends.name: The One With Mrs. Bing
friends.summary: Chandler's novelist mother visits -- and hits on Ross; Phoebe and Monica fall for the same guy.

friends.name: The One With the Dozen Lasagnas
friends.summary: Phoebe has some bad news for Rachel about Paolo; Ross learns some of the results of his former wife's amniocentesis.

friends.name: The One With the Boobies
friends.summary: Chandler sees Rachel naked; Joey learns his father is having an affair; Phoebe dates a psychiatrist.

friends.name: The One With the Candy Hearts
friends.summary:
Chandler has a blind date with an ex-girlfriend -- whom he's broken up 
with twice before; the ladies light a "boyfriend bonfire"; Ross finds an
 unlikely Valentine's Day date.

friends.name: The One With the Stoned Guy
friends.summary: Chandler and Monica plan big career moves, while Ross labors to hit it off with a date.

friends.name: The One With Two Parts (1)
friends.summary: Ross attends Lamaze classes; Joey dates Phoebe's twin; and Chandler has the hots for a co-worker he's supposed to fire.

friends.name: The One With Two Parts (2)
friends.summary: Monica and Rachel meet two cute doctors; Ross looks to Jack for fatherly advice; Phoebe confronts her twin about Joey.

friends.name: The One With All the Poker
friends.summary: The guys let the ladies in on a sacred ritual -- their poker game. Meanwhile, Rachel has an interview with Saks.

friends.name: The One Where the Monkey Gets Away
friends.summary: Ross entrusts Rachel with his pet monkey for a day; Barry has a surprise for Rachel.

friends.name: The One With the Evil Orthodontist
friends.summary:
Chandler's not a very smooth operator when it comes to calling a woman 
he went out with; Rachel gets involved with her ex-fianc√©.

friends.name: The One With the Fake Monica
friends.summary: Monica meets the woman who used her credit-card number; Ross realizes it's time to find a new home for Marcel.

friends.name: The One With the Ick Factor
friends.summary: Phoebe gets temporary work as Chandler's secretary; Monica's new boyfriend is younger than she thinks.

friends.name: The One With the Birth
friends.summary: Ross quarrels with Susan in the delivery room as Carol prepares to give birth; Joey befriends a mother-to-be.

friends.name: The One Where Rachel Finds Out
friends.summary: Rachel finally realizes how much Ross likes her -- but not before he leaves for China on museum business.

friends.name: The One With Ross's New Girlfriend
friends.summary:
Rachel meets Ross's female travel companion; Joey unwittingly recommends
 a seamy tailor to Chandler; and Phoebe cuts Monica's hair.

friends.name: The One With the Breast Milk
friends.summary: Monica goes shopping with Julie behind Rachel's back; Ross isn't exactly gaga over breast milk.

friends.name: The One Where Heckles Dies
friends.summary: The gang disturbs Mr. Heckles for the last time; Phoebe takes issue with Ross on the subject of evolution.

friends.name: The One With Phoebe's Husband
friends.summary: Phoebe's secret husband shows up; Rachel tries to distract Ross from having sex with Julie.

friends.name: The One With Five Steaks and an Eggplant
friends.summary: Chandler receives a sexy phone call meant for someone else; the gang becomes divided along income lines.

friends.name: The One With the Baby on the Bus
friends.summary:
An allergic reaction sends Ross to the hospital, leaving Chandler and 
Joey to look after Ben; Central Perk hires another singer to replace Phoebe.

friends.name: The One Where Ross Finds Out
friends.summary: Rachel goes on a date in an effort to forget about Ross; Monica presses Chandler to complete an exercise program.

friends.name: The One With the List
friends.summary:
Ross is torn between Rachel and Julie, so Chandler prompts him to list 
each woman's pros and cons; Monica concocts recipes for a new product.

friends.name: The One With Phoebe's Dad
friends.summary: Phoebe confronts her grandmother about the father she never knew; things heat up at Monica's holiday party.

friends.name: The One With Russ
friends.summary:
Rachel dates a guy who's similar to Ross; Joey can get a part if he 
sleeps with the casting director; Fun Bobby is no fun without alcohol.

friends.name: The One With the Lesbian Wedding
friends.summary:
Rachel's mother considers ending her marriage; Carol 
decides to marry her lover, Susan; Phoebe believes she's possessed.

friends.name: The One After the Superbowl (1)
friends.summary: Ross searches for Marcel; Joey is attracted to an obsessed fan; Phoebe sings songs for kids.

friends.name: The One After the Superbowl (2)
friends.summary:
Ross learns Marcel is working on a movie, and the film's makeup artist 
seems to want Chandler; Monica and Rachel fight over Jean-Claude Van 
Damme, who appears as himself.

friends.name: The One With the Prom Video
friends.summary:
Monica brings some things home from her parents' house, including a prom
 video; Rachel tells Ross that she doesn't think it will work out 
between them.

friends.name: The One Where Ross and Rachel... You Know
friends.summary:
Ross's work hinders the evolution of his and Rachel's romance; Monica 
has eyes for an older opthalmologist; Joey and Chandler 
enjoy a big-screen TV.

friends.name: The One Where Joey Moves Out
friends.summary:
Richard's relationship with a younger woman causes a stir at a party for
 Ross and Monica's dad; Joey decides to move out; Rachel gets a tattoo.

friends.name: The One Where Eddie Moves In
friends.summary: Chandler gets a new roommate; Monica doesn't like having Ross around all the time; Phoebe makes a music video.

friends.name: The One Where Dr. Ramoray Dies
friends.summary: The days in the life of Joey's character, Dr. Ramoray, are numbered; Chandler's new roommate scares him.

friends.name: The One Where Eddie Won't Go
friends.summary: Chandler wants Eddie to move out; Joey faces unemployment; a self-help book empowers the ladies.

friends.name: The One Where Old Yeller Dies
The One With the Bullies
friends.summary: Bullies accost Ross and Chandler; Monica plays the stock market; and Phoebe attempts to meet her father again.

friends.name: The One With the Two Parties
friends.summary: When Rachel's divorcing parents both show up for her birthday, her friends hold two separate parties to keep them apart.

friends.name: The One With the Chicken Pox
friends.summary:
A submariner surfaces to spend two weeks with Phoebe, 
who's come down with chicken pox; Joey plays the role of a data 
processor at Chandler's company.

friends.name: The One With Barry and Mindy's Wedding
friends.summary: Rachel's in her ex-fianc√©'s wedding; Chandler has a cyberspace romance; Monica and Richard think about their future.

friends.name: The One With the Princess Leia Fantasy
friends.summary:
Janice tries to change Joey's opinion of her; Ross's sexual fantasy 
isn't kept between him and Rachel; Monica can't shake memories of 
Richard.

friends.name: The One Where No One's Ready
friends.summary: Nobody seems to be getting the message when Ross demands that the group get ready for his black-tie benefit.

friends.name: The One With the Jam
friends.summary: Monica turns her attention from making jam to maybe making a baby; Phoebe befriends a guy who's stalking her twin sister.

friends.name: The One With the Metaphorical Tunnel
friends.summary: Chandler decides to make a real commitment to Janice; Phoebe poses as Joey's agent; Ross is troubled by Ben's toy.

friends.name: The One With Frank Jr.
friends.summary:
The gang compiles "freebie lists"; Phoebe tries to get to know her half 
brother; Joey builds an entertainment center.

friends.name: The One With the Flashback
friends.summary: The show flashes back to when the friends were acquaintances and pairing off was a possibility.

friends.name: The One With the Race Car Bed
The One With the Giant Poking Device
friends.summary:
Joey reveals to Chandler that he saw Janice kissing her estranged 
husband; Rachel and Monica baby-sit Ben; Phoebe explains her fear of the
 dentist.

friends.name: The One With the Football
friends.summary: Ross and Monica go nose-to-nose in an unfriendly Thanksgiving football game.

friends.name: The One Where Rachel Quits
friends.summary:
Rachel quits Central Perk; Phoebe objects to the treatment of Christmas 
trees; Ross sells cookies for a "Brown Bird" scout he injured; Monica 
gets hooked on Mint Treasures.

friends.name: The One Where Chandler Can't Remember Which Sister
friends.summary: A drunken Chandler has a liaison with one of Joey's sisters; a nice guy recommends Rachel for a job.

friends.name: The One With All the Jealousy
friends.summary: Ross is jealous of Mark; a romantic poet criticizes Monica in verse; Joey's a dancing fool for a Broadway musical audition.

friends.name: The One Where Monica and Richard are Just Friends
friends.summary:
Monica sees Richard again and they agree to be just 
pals -- and occasional lovers; Phoebe's new beau has an embarrassing 
habit.

friends.name: The One With Phoebe's Ex-Partner
friends.summary:
Phoebe's ex-singing partner wants to reunite; Chandler likes a woman associated with a shameful incident from Joey's past; 
Ross wants to spend more time with Rachel.

friends.name: The One Where Ross and Rachel Take a Break
friends.summary: Ross and Rachel decide to take a break in their relationship; Phoebe dates a diplomat who requires a translator.

friends.name: The One the Morning After
friends.summary:
Ross's fling with Chloe jeopardizes his future with Rachel, who learns 
of the misdeed after she says she wants to work things out.

friends.name: The One Without the Ski Trip
friends.summary: Rachel organizes a ski trip for all the friends except Ross, who must then come to their rescue when they run out of gas.

friends.name: The One With the Hypnosis Tape
friends.summary:
Phoebe's upset by her brother's engagement to an older woman; Monica 
dates a computer-software mogul; Chandler tries to quit 
smoking.

friends.name: The One With the Tiny T-Shirt
friends.summary:
Mark asks out Rachel, who returns Ross's things; Monica still isn't 
attracted to millionaire Pete; Joey's irked by his costar in a play.

friends.name: The One With the Dollhouse
friends.summary:
Chandler's insincere "I'll call you" to Rachel's boss causes 
complications; Monica inherits a dollhouse; Joey and Kate get romantic.

friends.name: The One With a Chick and a Duck
friends.summary:
Ross helps an injured Rachel prepare for a business dinner, but doesn't 
tell her he's missing a chance to appear on TV; Pete buys 
Monica a restaurant; Chandler and Joey adopt a baby chick.

friends.name: The One With the Screamer
friends.summary:
Chandler's insincere "I'll call you" to Rachel's boss causes 
complications; Monica inherits a dollhouse; Joey and Kate get romantic.

friends.name: The One With Ross's Thing
friends.summary: Ross has an unusual growth; Phoebe is torn between two men she's dating; Monica thinks Pete is going to propose.

friends.name: The One With the Ultimate Fighting Champion
friends.summary: Pete pursues the Ultimate Fighting championship; Chandler has a slap-happy new boss; Ross dates Phoebe's friend.

friends.name: The One at the Beach
The One With the Jellyfish
friends.summary:
At the beach house, Ross and Rachel appear on the threshold of a new 
era; Phoebe gets to know her birth mother (Teri Garr); Monica is stung 
by a jellyfish.

friends.name: The One With the Cat
friends.summary:
Phoebe thinks her mother's spirit resides in a cat; Monica dates a 
former high-school hunk; Joey tries to sell the entertainment center.

friends.name: The One With the 'Cuffs
friends.summary: Chandler's torrid fling with Rachel's boss (Alison LaPlaca) puts him in a compromising position; Monica caters her mom's party.

friends.name: The One With the Ballroom Dancing
friends.summary: Joey' s roped into being the superintendent's practice dance partner; Phoebe gets fired.

friends.name: The One With Joey's New Girlfriend
friends.summary: Chandler falls for Joey's new girlfriend (Paget Brewster); Phoebe likes the effect of a cold on her singing voice.

friends.name: The One With the Dirty Girl
friends.summary: Phoebe helps Monica cater a funeral; Chandler buys Kathy a special birthday gift; Ross's beautiful date has a very messy place.

friends.name: The One Where Chandler Crosses the Line
friends.summary: Chandler keeps Kathy (Paget Brewster) company while Joey's out with another girl---and one thing leads to another.

friends.name: The One With Chandler in a Box
friends.summary: On Thanksgiving, Chandler begs for Joey's forgiveness about Kathy (Paget Brewster); Monica has eyes for Richard's son.

friends.name: The One Where They're Going to Party!
friends.summary:
Rachel is promised a promotion; a restaurateur confronts Monica after 
she writes a scathing review; Chandler and Ross prepare to party with a 
world-class carouser.

friends.name: The One With the Girl from Poughkeepsie
The One With Phoebe's Uterus
friends.summary:
In lieu of a gift, newlyweds Frank Jr. and Alice (Giovanni Ribisi, Debra
 Jo Rupp) ask Phoebe to be a surrogate mother for their child; Ross 
breaks an unwritten rule at the museum.

friends.name: The One With the Embryos
friends.summary:
Phoebe undergoes in-vitro fertilization; Monica and Rachel go up against
 Joey and Chandler to determine which pair know the other better.

friends.name: The One With Rachel's Crush
friends.summary: Kathy's sexy role in a play irks Chandler; personal-shopper Rachel develops a crush on a client.

friends.name: The One With Joey's Dirty Day
friends.summary:
Joey doesn't smell too good when he's about to appear in a Charlton 
Heston movie; Rachel asks Ross to entertain her boss's niece so she can 
be with Joshua; the girls join heartbroken Chandler at a strip joint.

friends.name: The One With All the Rugby
friends.summary:
Ross plays rugby to impress Emily; to escape Janice, Chandler claims 
he's being transferred; Monica obsesses over a useless switch.

friends.name: The One With the Fake Party
friends.summary:
Rachel throws an impromptu going-away party for Emily to lure Joshua 
into a social setting; pregnant vegetarian Phoebe craves meat.

friends.name: The One With the Free Porn
friends.summary: Ross pursues his romance with Emily (Helen Baxendale); Phoebe learns she's having triplets; the boys get free adult TV.

friends.name: The One With Rachel's New Dress
friends.summary:
Rachel gears up for a night of romance with Joshua; Ross fears Emily is 
getting too chummy with Susan; Phoebe names one of the triplets.

friends.name: The One With All the Haste
friends.summary: Ross proposes to Emily (Helen Baxendale); Rachel and Monica demand their apartment back from the guys.

friends.name: The One With All the Wedding Dresses
friends.summary: Monica tries on Emily's wedding dress; Ross's plans affect Rachel and Joshua; Chandler insists Joey get help for his snoring.

friends.name: The One With the Invitation
friends.summary: In a clip show, Rachel receives her invitation to Ross and Emily's wedding.

friends.name: The One With the Worst Best Man Ever
friends.summary: Best man Joey (Matt LeBlanc) loses Ross's heirloom ring; pregnant Phoebe has mood swings.

friends.name: The One With Ross's Wedding: Part I
friends.summary: London's the location for Ross and Emily's wedding, but back at home, Rachel realizes that she still loves the groom-to-be.

friends.name: The One With Ross's Wedding: Part II
friends.summary:
As Ross and Emily prepare to wed, Rachel makes a frantic attempt to 
reach London before the ceremony. Elsewhere, there is no love lost 
between Ross's and Emily's fathers.

friends.name: The One After Ross Says Rachel
friends.summary:
Ross and Rachel cope with the ramifications of Ross saying "Rachel" 
instead of "Emily" during his wedding vows; Monica and Chandler are 
still hot for each other.

friends.name: The One With All the Kissing
friends.summary:
Rachel wants to tell Ross that she still loves him; Chandler must buss 
Rachel and Phoebe to cover up a kiss with Monica; Phoebe's water breaks.

friends.name: The One Hundredth
friends.summary: Phoebe's pregnancy comes to fruition; Monica and Chandler have their first fight.

friends.name: The One Where Phoebe Hates PBS
friends.summary: Phoebe reveals her hatred of PBS; Emily tells Ross she'll see him again---if he stops seeing Rachel.

friends.name: The One With the Kips
friends.summary: Monica and Chandler plan a weekend getaway; Ross has to tell Rachel that to save his marriage he can't see her anymore.

friends.name: The One With the Yeti
friends.summary: Emily's demands regarding Rachel weigh on Ross; Rachel and Monica encounter a hairy, beastlike man; Phoebe receives a fur coat.

friends.name: The One Where Ross Moves In
friends.summary: Ross moves in with the boys; Phoebe dates a health inspector; Rachel plays hard to get for Danny, who's oblivious.

friends.name: The One With All the Thanksgivings
friends.summary: The gang reflects on bad Thanksgivings---and the biggest turkey belongs to Monica, who recalls her first encounter with Chandler.

friends.name: The One With Ross's Sandwich
friends.summary:
Ross loses it when someone eats his sandwich at work; keeping up 
appearances for Monica and Chandler makes Joey look bad; Phoebe and 
Rachel take a lit class.

friends.name: The One With the Inappropriate Sister
friends.summary:
Danny's close relationship with his sister (Julie Lauren) bothers 
Rachel; Ross urges Joey to write a script; Phoebe collects for holiday 
charity on a street corner.

friends.name: The One With All the Resolutions
friends.summary: Rachel's New Year's resolution not to gossip is tested when she discovers Monica and Chandler's romance.

friends.name: The One With Chandler's Work Laugh
friends.summary: Monica meets "Work Chandler"; Ross gets together with Janice.

friends.name: The One With Joey's Bag
friends.summary: Phoebe meets Frank Sr. (Bob Balaban) at her grandma's funeral; Joey gets attached to a bag that's like a purse.

friends.name: The One Where Everybody Finds Out
friends.summary: Phoebe finds out about Monica and Chandler's romance; Ross plans to rent Ugly Naked Guy's apartment.

friends.name: The One With the Girl Who Hits Joey
friends.summary:
Chandler freaks out over the subject of marriage to Monica; Joey's 
girlfriend throws playful, but painful, punches; Ross alienates his new 
neighbors.

friends.name: The One With the Cop
friends.summary: Phoebe finds a police badge; Joey has a romantic dream about Monica; Rachel helps Ross move his new couch.

friends.name: The One With Rachel's Inadvertent Kiss
friends.summary: Rachel makes an awkward move during a job interview; Monica and Chandler compete with Phoebe and Gary to be the hotter couple.

friends.name: The One Where Rachel Smokes
friends.summary: Rachel takes up smoking for work reasons; Joey angles into an audition involving Ross's son, Ben.

friends.name: The One Where Ross Can't Flirt
friends.summary: Ross's flirting with the pizza-delivery girl falls flat; Joey's scene in a TV crime drama is cut.

friends.name: The One With the Ride Along
friends.summary: The boys ride along with Gary (Michael Rapaport); Monica and Rachel overhear bride-to-be Emily's urgent phone message to Ross.

friends.name: The One With the Ball
friends.summary: Gary (Michael Rapaport) asks Phoebe to live with him; a game of catch goes on for hours; Rachel buys an expensive cat.

friends.name: The One With Joey's Big Break
friends.summary: Joey is cast in an independent film to be shot in the desert outside Las Vegas; Phoebe's angry with Ross.

friends.name: The One in Vegas (1)
friends.summary:
Chandler and Monica celebrate their first anniversary; the gang goes to 
Vegas to visit Joey; Chandler finds out about Monica's lunch with 
Richard.

friends.name: The One in Vegas (2)
friends.summary:
In Vegas, Monica and Chandler reconcile and literally roll the dice on 
whether to get married, while one couple actually do tie the knot.
